{"type":"message","id":"63ff05a3","parentId":"d24fd032","timestamp":"2026-03-24T14:13:22.263Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I have the full picture. Let me write a concise summary.","thinkingSignature":"36054ef72eff52c7ec8cd5bc605d5a0094460442a3d1e2152b231e2f24b1db86"},{"type":"text","text":"## Sandbox Pulse Summary — 2026-03-24 10:12 AM\n\n**✅ Completed: CFI Analysis** — Analyzed frequency-invariants across 12 pulses. Key finding: 94.3% of invariants are noise (CFI<0.7), with 44.8% having CFI=0 (pure noise artifacts). Only ~5.7% are true causal anchors.\n\n**🔬 Proposed Mutation** — New experiment: `research/CFI_COMPRESSION_EXPERIMENT.md`\n- Hypothesis: Filtering invariants by CFI score will improve compression vs. frequency-only baseline\n- Test: CFI-weighted selection vs. frequency baseline for next-pulse prediction\n- Status: **Awaiting implementation** (1 proposed mutation in queue)\n\n**📊 Git Status** — 6 files changed, +239 insertions, -43 deletions. Previous mutation (`Grok-analysis-integration.md`) was **rejected** (renamed to `mutations/rejected/`).\n\n**Next step for sandbox:** Implement the CFI-weighted compression experiment to test whether CFI filtering actually improves prediction quality."}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":1443,"output":244,"cacheRead":12137,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":13824,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1774361594440}}
